1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with face attribute manipulation using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and image transformation networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel approach to learning residual images for attribute manipulation. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses GANs to generate images with specific attributes, which is a common application of AI. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with image manipulation and transformation. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is also a possible category as the paper deals with generating and manipulating images.
